      • processQueries

        public void processQueries(Collection<? extends Query<I,O>> queries)
        Description copied from interface: MembershipOracle
        Processes the specified collection of queries. When this method returns, the output field of each of the contained queries should reflect the SUL response to the respective query.
        Specified by:
        processQueries in interface MembershipOracle<I,O>
        Parameters:
        queries - the queries to process
        See Also:
        DefaultQuery.getOutput()

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stop all worker threads. After this method has been called, invoking processQueries(Collection) will result in an IllegalStateException until the next call to start() is made.
